DAC_A_lastchange: DAC PMT A  HV setting date/time of last change

DAC_A_max_volt: Max volt on DAC PMT A

DAC_B_min_volt: Min volt on DAC  PMT B
DAC_B_max_volt: Max volt on DAC PMT B
Dead_time: Dead time from NI pulser measurement
Total_counts_last_minute: Number of counts since last minute
Total_counts_this_run: Number of counts since start of run
Time_offset_manual: Known manual timing offset in nsec
Element_for_Calibration: Use this element for gain calibration
Digitizer_full_range: set the full range to 2 or 4 volt
input_offset_target: Input offset  target; where the baseline should be
FPGA_master_gate_low: FPGA gate setting  master gate low

FPGA_master_gate_high_ch: FPGA gate setting  master gate high
Threshold_mV: Software peakheight threshold to be counted
Weighting_gain: Cluster Weighting gain factor for this detector
Gamma_tail_low: Gamma-tail ratio for gamma acceptance gate low
Gamma_tail_high: Gamma-tail ratio for gamma acceptance gate high
Neutron_tail_low: Neutron PSD tail ration for neutron acceptance low
Neutron_tail_high: Neutron PSD tail ration for neutron acceptance high

Trigger_to_gamma_ratio: Displays events rejected by pilup etc
Tail_short_needed_low: Tail 1 fraction to total tail 1+2+3 low

Pulse_height_gain: Gain for pulse height histogram Channel/mV

Timing_spectrum_length: Timing spectrum length for this channel
Pulse_shape_spectrum_length: Pulse shape spectrum length for this channel
GN_2D_length_X: X-plot length for 2D neutron gamma plot
GN_2D_length_Y: Y-plot length for 2D neutron gamma plot

Det_Group: Or NaI; Ge; Specify a name

DAC_A_to Histgram_gain: So we are right on correcting the HV
DAC_B_HV_setting: The DAC setting to givr the right HV
DAC_B_to Histgram_gain: So we are right on correcting the HV
Signal_integral: Integrate over all pulses Pulse_integral ns*channels
Time_offset_changed: Make a note when it was calibrated

input_offset_target: in percent of fullscale range;  should be about 7%

Input_offset_value: where the calibration put the offset in digitizer counts

Input_invert: Invert the input before processing;  Invert= -1;  non = 1

Pulse_height_gain: So the overflow is still visible

Pulse_shape_spectrum_length: 128 ch  up to 16k peak in center
GN_2D_length_X: 128 ch  up to 16k peak in center
GN_2D_length_Y: 128 ch  up to 16k peak in center
GN_2D_gain_X: So all events fit on the 2D plot
GN_2D_gain_Y: So all events fit on the 2D plot
